The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Neutral venues
                                                   Neutral venues
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Headingley and Lords were given hosting rights to next years Test series between Australia and Pakistan on Friday.         
	The ECB switched Englands first Test against Bangladesh to Old Trafford to allow the series to be partly held at Headingley. Lords will host the other match of each series.         
	In 2011, the Twenty20 Internationals against India and Sri Lanka will held be at Old Trafford and Bristol respectively.         
	Meanwhile, the results of an inquiry into the abandonment of this months Twenty20 at Old Trafford between England and Australia were released Friday. They include a recommendation that drainage facilities and permanent floodlights should be given increased consideration when choosing venues.                                                                                                                       
